1. Class and object
* Class is an blueprint of an object.
* It defines the properties and behaviours of an object.
* It encapsulates data and functions into a single unit.
* Object is an instance of a class.
* objects are created based on the structure defined in the class.


2. Oops and features

Oops--> is a programming approach based on the concept of objects,
*The key aim of OOP is to model real-world entities more naturally and efficiently in code.

Features of oops

* Encapsulation.
* Abstraction.
* Inheritance.
* Polymorphism.
* Class and Object.
